BACKTRACKING FOR SUDOKU

ISVALID(BOARD,ROW,COL,NUM)

  1. Repeat the following for x=0 to x=8
    a. Do if BOARD[x][COL] is NUM
      i. Return false

  2. Repeat the following for x=0 to x=8
    a. Do if BOARD[ROW][x] is NUM
      i. Return false

  3. Set ROW as ROW-ROW modulus 3 and 
      Set COL as COL-COL modulus 3

  4. Repeat the following for i=0 to i<3
    b. Repeat the following for j=0 to j<3
      i. Return false if BOARD[i+ROW][j+COL] is NUM

  5. Return true
  
  
SOLVER(BOARD,ROW,COL)

  1.Set length of the BOARD as N

  2. Do if ROW is N and COL is N
    a. Return true

  3. Do if COL is N
    a. COL=0
    b. ROW=ROW+1

  4. Do if BOARD[ROW][COL]>0
    a. Return SOLVER(BOARD,ROW,COL+1)

  5. Repeat the following for NUM=1 to NUM=N
    a. Do if ISVALID(BOARD,ROW,COL+1)
      i.    BOARD[ROW][COL]=NUM
      ii.   Return true if SOLVER(BOARD,ROW,COL+1) is true
      iii.  BOARD[ROW][COL]=0

  6. Return true
